post_text:
LCSD 55 ANNOUNCES REOPENING PHASE FOR SEPTEMBER 8
According to the latest community spread levels reported on August 24 by DHEC, Laurens County’s spread risk of COVID-19 is currently ranked as moderate. This means that the school district will start school on September 8 in the Hybrid Learning Phase (Yellow Phase). For the first week of school, students on the Green Team will attend on Tuesday, September 8, and Wednesday, September 9. Students on the Gold Team will attend on Thursday, September 10, and Friday, September 11. Anyone unsure of their assigned team should contact their school. The Hybrid Phase means having fewer students in the building each day, lessening the risk of transmission, and allowing for six feet social distancing. If there are any significant changes in the community spread level resulting in a need to change the opening phase, an announcement will be made as quickly as possible.

On Tuesday, August 18, 2020, from 6:30 – 7:30 p.m., the Laurens County Virtual Academy (LCVA) will be hosting a virtual meeting for the parents of elementary age children who have registered for LCVA. The meeting will preview the EdMentum and Calvert learning systems that will be used for elementary LCVA students.

This meeting is only for elementary parents whose children will be attending LCVA during the first semester (or for those on the waiting list for LCVA). This information is not applicable to the model of eLearning that will be utilized for non-LCVA students when Laurens County School District #55 (LCSD 55) is in a RED (all eLearning) or YELLOW (hybrid) phase instructional environment.

Parents interested in attending this virtual meeting must register at LCVA Elementary Parent Meeting on the LCSD 55 website at www.laurens55.org to receive a link to the meeting. For those parents unable to attend on August 18th, a video recording of the meeting will be made available as soon as possible after the meeting.

post_text: LCSD 55 is asking families who wish to elect LCVA for the 2020-2021 school year to complete their registration form(s) by tomorrow Friday, July 24, 2020. Laurens County School District #55 will publish The LCSD 55 Returns Plan Book soon. The handbook will share plans for health, safety, and learning throughout LCSD 55. The handbook for re-opening schools is directed by guidelines set by local, state, and federal governments and public health officials’ recommendations. LCSD 55 has not yet received final approval from the State Superintendent on re-opening plans. The district understands how eager the community is to learn about what schools will look like starting Tuesday, September 8, 2020, the first official day back to school.
LCSD 55 would like to thank the community for their patience as the Board of Trustees, Superintendent, and LCSD 55 leadership teams, teachers, and staff are working as fast as possible to provide the community with accurate and approved descriptions of what the beginning of the year will entail.
You will be able to locate the LCSD 55 Returns Plan Book on the district website at www.laurens55.org soon.

post_text:
Greetings! I am incredibly proud, honored, and humbled to be selected by the Board of Trustees to lead Laurens County School District 55. I have worked in the district in many different roles, and I am excited about my new role as superintendent. With a sense of calculated urgency, Laurens 55 students, staff, and community will be a top priority! I am enthusiastic about this work. In pursuit of excellence, equity, and access for each student, I will show up each day with an unwavering commitment to service.

I look forward to working with all L55 stakeholders!
While I know this is a challenging time for us all, I am excited about the future!

Today, Monday, June 22, is the last day to fill out the LCSD 55 parent survey. Feedback from the parent survey will help provide a framework for how the district adapts its resources, personnel, and teaching models to a COVID-19 world. LCSD 55 parents can access the survey online or pick up a paper copy of the survey at any of the individual LCSD 55 schools. All paper copies must be returned today to any LCSD 55 school. Parents are invited to complete the survey by using the computer located in the front lobby of the District Office.

To access the parent survey, click here https://forms.gle/jLqEEUY8qxoqJJfW7

This count affects the allocation of billions of dollars of federal education aid to states and localities using formulas that factor in population and poverty levels. Today is the day to complete your household census. Go to: https://my2020census.gov/login.
A successful day today will go a long way in helping us receive the help we need.

Today is the 2020 Census Day of Action! Together South Carolina is committed to raising awareness about the 2020 Census and its completion. Lt. Governor Evette said, "I'm challenging all South Carolinians across the state to improve South Carolina's rate of completion. Our goal is for 10,000 households to complete the census on this date – that's approximately two hundred households per county, which would be about a 2% increase overall."

There are many resources available to provide information and facts and to answer any questions regarding the U.S. Census. To begin completing your household census, go to https://my2020census.gov/login. For more general information, visit www.census.gov.

#SCCounts2020 #CountMeInSC #CensusDayofAction

Parent Survey on E-Learning and Re-entry

Laurens County School District #55 (LCSD 55) has begun work on a plan addressing the following issues: e-learning, re-entry, curriculum and instruction, special population needs, and operational procedures. LCSD 55 is surveying parents on their thoughts and ideas regarding e-Learning and the Re-entry plan for fall 2020.

Feedback from the parent survey will help provide a framework for how the district adapts its resources, personnel, and teaching models to a COVID-19 world. LCSD 55 asks all parents to complete the survey by Monday, June 15, 2020.
To access the parent survey, click here https://forms.gle/jLqEEUY8qxoqJJfW7

Laurens District 55 High School (LDHS) graduation will be held tomorrow, Thursday, June 4, 2020, at K.C. Hanna Stadium at 10:00 AM. The safety of students, families, and faculty are of the utmost importance. Please respect social distancing guidelines, and refrain from entering graduation if you are experiencing any of the following symptoms, and/or have come into contact with someone who has tested positive for COVID-19 in the last two weeks.

FEVER, COUGH, CHILLS, MUSCLE PAIN, SHORTNESS OF BREATH, SORE THROAT, NEW LOSS OF TASTE OR SMELL

Thank you, we look forward to celebrating the class of 2020!

Live-Stream Viewing:
For those who cannot attend, the ceremony will stream live at the following link: http://allmondphotovideo.com/graduation.html. Please note that the link will only be live at the time of the ceremony. Prior to the event, the message “Event Has Been Deleted” will be on display.

LCSD 55 will consolidate regularly scheduled meal pick up for E.B. Morse Elementary with meal pick-up at Laurens Middle School. Meals will not be available at the E.B. Morse Elementary location on Thursday. Instead, meal pickups for E.B. Morse students and families will be at Laurens Middle School, 1035 W Main St, Laurens, SC 29360, from 11:00 am to 12:00 pm on Thursday, May 21, 2020.

In addition, due to the Memorial Day holiday, the Thursday meal pick up (May 21, 2020) will include meals for Thursday through Monday. There will be no meal distribution on Memorial Day, Monday, May 25, 2020. Instead, meal pick up next week will be on Tuesday, May 26, and Thursday, May 28, 2020.

The district hopes this notice will allow families the time to plan accordingly for both the change in location and the holiday weekend.

The Miss South Carolina Organization is "Crowning" COVID-19 HEROS, and Laurens District 55 High School (LDHS) student - Kaley Bridgeman has crowned two Laurens County School District 55 (LCSD 55) teachers, JD Huff and Amanda Lloyd.

Miss South Carolina 2019 Morgan Nichols came up with this idea of "crowning" or placing gold ribbons on mailboxes or buildings of those in the community who deserve recognition during this Coronavirus pandemic.

Bridgeman, the Miss Greenville County Teen 2020, said, "I wanted to crown these teachers because they have done a phenomenal job ensuring I understand the material. They care about how I am doing every day."

post_text: Dr. Anna Brink will become LCSD 55’s new Director of Federal Programs, Accountability, and Professional Development (FPAPD). This move will provide some relief to Dr. Jody Penland, the Assistant Superintendent for Pupil Personnel Services, who has been playing a dual role since his promotion earlier this school year. Penland, will continue to provide guidance in the FPAPD Department as Dr. Brink takes on the challenges of her new role. In responding to the news of her selection, Brink said, “"I have been blessed to be a part of this district, which I grew up in and graduated from, and I look forward to continuing to serve in this new role. Thank you to the school board and the district administration for giving me this opportunity and I know great things will continue in LCSD 55.”
text: Dr. Anna Brink will become LCSD 55’s new Director of Federal Programs, Accountability, and Professional Development (FPAPD). This move will provide some relief to Dr. Jody Penland, the Assistant Superintendent for Pupil Personnel Services, who has been playing a dual role since his promotion earlier this school year. Penland, will continue to provide guidance in the FPAPD Department as Dr. Brink takes on the challenges of her new role. In responding to the news of her selection, Brink said, “"I have been blessed to be a part of this district, which I grew up in and graduated from, and I look forward to continuing to serve in this new role. Thank you to the school board and the district administration for giving me this opportunity and I know great things will continue in LCSD 55.”

post_text: Dr. Rhett Harris, the current Director of Operations, will assume additional responsibilities as the new Director of Secondary Education (while retaining his leadership responsibilities in operations). Harris was the long-time Principal at Laurens Middle School before moving to the district office in 2018. He has led efforts to improve building security and remove the former P&T hardware building recently acquired by LCSD 55. Following the Board’s approval, Harris said, “I'm very honored to have been given new responsibilities in the Office of Teaching and Learning. I look forward to working with the High School and all middle schools to help provide our students with the very best in educational practices."

Respond to the 2020 Census now!
•Respond at my2020census.gov or call the toll-free number (844-330-2020) listed on your invitation.
•Use the Census ID included in your invitation. You can also respond without it by providing your address.
•Or, if you received a paper questionnaire, fill it out and mail it back (you can respond online if you prefer).
•Include everyone living in your home as of April 1st, 2020.

Today, Thursday, March 26, 2020, Student Nutrition Services will pack four meals for pick up (two lunches and two breakfasts), and there will be no pick up of meals on Friday. The same process will be used on Monday (packing lunch and breakfast for both Monday and Tuesday) with no pick up of meals on Tuesday. LCSD 55 will deliver six meals (three lunches and three breakfasts) on Wednesday, April 1, 2020. After that, for as long as the schools remain closed, LCSD 55 will be packaging meals for pick up every Monday (four meals) and Wednesday (six meals). Meals will continue to be available at selected bus stops throughout LCSD 55.

Meal packages can be picked up at any school location between 11am-12pm on select days of the week. For bus, delivery locations visit https://www.laurens55.org/

post_text:
It’s the year of the 2020 U.S. Census. The U.S. Census Bureau counts everyone living in the United States, including every child. The impact of COVID-19 presents a unique opportunity for parents to teach their students about self-worth, civic engagement, and the value of data—and to promote a complete count that will benefit Laurens County School District #55 (LCSD 55) schools for the next ten years.

Please take the time to involve your children as you fill out the U.S. Census. There are lots of resources available to provide information, facts, and to answer any questions regarding the U.S. Census. To begin completing your household census, go to: https://my2020census.gov/login. For more general information visit: www.census.gov.

post_text: Starting Tuesday, March 17, 2020, the Laurens County School District #55 (LCSD 55) custodians began working their way through each school completing a thorough cleaning. This work in all LCSD 55 schools will be completed today, Tuesday, March 24, 2020. Now, staff will turn their attention to other areas of need. "The work that has been done over the last week has been a great team effort," said Dr. Rhett Harris, Director of Operations. "Keith Bailey and David Turner have provided significant leadership in getting this work done and done at a high standard." Please be sure to thank all the men and women who have continued their hard work and service to LCSD 55 in this difficult time. This includes not only custodial staff but also our maintenance workers, student nutrition services personnel, and select personnel in each school and the district office. We thank you all!

post_text:
Laurens County School District #55 (LCSD 55) would like to remind parents and students of Daylight Savings time on Sunday, March 8, 2020. We will spring forward and clocks should be set one hour forward. On Friday, March 13, 2020, LCSD 55 schools and offices will be closed. The day was initially marked as a make-up day on the district calendar in case of emergencies or inclement weather.

LCSD 55 students will have an early release day on Thursday, March 12, 2020, and no school on Friday, March 13, 2020, or Monday, March 16, 2020. Some staff will be involved in professional development activities on Monday, March 16, 2020, and LCSD 55 offices will be sponsoring the State of the Schools Luncheon and Fundraiser at The Ridge at Laurens from 12:00 p.m. to 2:00 p.m.

By state law, school districts are required to include three potential make-up days in their calendar every year. The remaining make-up day for LSCD 55 is scheduled for Monday, April 13, 2020. The district will continue to communicate information about other adjustments in the calendar if they occur.

post_text: Public Schools Week 2020 celebrates our nation's public schools, our students, and the many school professionals who work to help students achieve their greatest potential. A broad group of 10 million parents and educators — administrators, teachers, specialists, teacher educators, and school board members — will mark the week with events and outreach to their communities. In Washington, D.C., a bipartisan group of lawmakers will speak on the importance of a strong public education system for our country's future economic strength.

shared_text:
Laurens District 55 added 24 new photos.
February 12 at 2:52 PM ·

Laurens Middle School students now have the chance to engage in some hands-on learning thanks to new science labs. The new science labs, which were celebrated at a ribbon-cutting event today, February 12, 2020, feature new technology including microscopes and a Promethean smart board, as well as modern desks and safety equipment. This is the first new building added to the Laurens Campus since it opened its doors as Laurens High School in 1953. The students are excited about all of the experimentation and learning that will be taking place in their new science labs.
